(a) Fifteen persons were shortlisted for a job interview. On the day of the interview, each applicant was assigned a number from 1 to 15. An applicant was called at random from the list of numbers. Find the probability that the applicant called has a number that is:
(i) prime;
(ii) multiple of $3$;
(iii) divisible by $5$.
